label: The Beige Book
definition: The Summary of Commentary on Current Economic Conditions by Federal Reserve District. It is published eight times a year.
synonyms: Summary of Commentary on Current Economic Conditions

label: The Tealbook
definition: Report to the FOMC on Economic Conditions and Monetary Policy.

label: 10-K
definition: A comprehensive summary report of a company's financial performance that must be submitted annually to the Securities and Exchange Commission. It is more detailed than the annual report to shareholders.

label: 10-Q
definition: A comprehensive report of financial performance submitted quarterly to the SEC. It includes unaudited financial statements and provides a continuing view of the company's financial position during the year.

label: 8-K
definition: A report of unscheduled material events or corporate changes at a company that could be of importance to the shareholders or the SEC, such as acquisitions, bankruptcy, or C-suite changes.

label: S-1
definition: The initial registration form required by the SEC for US companies planning to go public (IPO).

label: FOMC Minutes
definition: The detailed record of the Federal Open Market Committee policy-setting meetings, released three weeks after the meeting. Traders scrutinize these for hawkish or dovish signals.
